171/* Commands understood by cmd_buffer ioctl. More can be added but
172 * obviously these can't be removed or changed:
173 */
174#define RADEON_CMD_PACKET 1 /* emit one of the register packets above */
175#define RADEON_CMD_SCALARS 2 /* emit scalar data */
176#define RADEON_CMD_VECTORS 3 /* emit vector data */
177#define RADEON_CMD_DMA_DISCARD 4 /* discard current dma buf */
178#define RADEON_CMD_PACKET3 5 /* emit hw packet */
179#define RADEON_CMD_PACKET3_CLIP 6 /* emit hw packet wrapped in cliprects */
180#define RADEON_CMD_SCALARS2 7 /* r200 stopgap */
181#define RADEON_CMD_WAIT 8 /* emit hw wait commands -- note:
182 * doesn't make the cpu wait, just
183 * the graphics hardware */
184#define RADEON_CMD_VECLINEAR 9 /* another r200 stopgap */
185
186typedef union {
187 int i;
188 struct {
189 unsigned char cmd_type, pad0, pad1, pad2;
190 } header;
191 struct {
192 unsigned char cmd_type, packet_id, pad0, pad1;
193 } packet;
194 struct {
195 unsigned char cmd_type, offset, stride, count;
196 } scalars;
197 struct {
198 unsigned char cmd_type, offset, stride, count;
199 } vectors;
200 struct {
201 unsigned char cmd_type, addr_lo, addr_hi, count;
202 } veclinear;
203 struct {
204 unsigned char cmd_type, buf_idx, pad0, pad1;
205 } dma;
206 struct {
207 unsigned char cmd_type, flags, pad0, pad1;
208 } wait;
209} drm_radeon_cmd_header_t;
210
211#define RADEON_WAIT_2D 0x1
212#define RADEON_WAIT_3D 0x2
213
214/* Allowed parameters for R300_CMD_PACKET3
215 */
216#define R300_CMD_PACKET3_CLEAR 0
217#define R300_CMD_PACKET3_RAW 1
218
219/* Commands understood by cmd_buffer ioctl for R300.
220 * The interface has not been stabilized, so some of these may be removed
221 * and eventually reordered before stabilization.
222 */
223#define R300_CMD_PACKET0 1
224#define R300_CMD_VPU 2 /* emit vertex program upload */
225#define R300_CMD_PACKET3 3 /* emit a packet3 */
226#define R300_CMD_END3D 4 /* emit sequence ending 3d rendering */
227#define R300_CMD_CP_DELAY 5
228#define R300_CMD_DMA_DISCARD 6
229#define R300_CMD_WAIT 7
230# define R300_WAIT_2D 0x1
231# define R300_WAIT_3D 0x2
232/* these two defines are DOING IT WRONG - however
233 * we have userspace which relies on using these.
234 * The wait interface is backwards compat new
235 * code should use the NEW_WAIT defines below
236 * THESE ARE NOT BIT FIELDS
237 */
238# define R300_WAIT_2D_CLEAN 0x3
239# define R300_WAIT_3D_CLEAN 0x4
240
241# define R300_NEW_WAIT_2D_3D 0x3
242# define R300_NEW_WAIT_2D_2D_CLEAN 0x4
243# define R300_NEW_WAIT_3D_3D_CLEAN 0x6
244# define R300_NEW_WAIT_2D_2D_CLEAN_3D_3D_CLEAN 0x8
245
246#define R300_CMD_SCRATCH 8
247#define R300_CMD_R500FP 9
248
249typedef union {
250 unsigned int u;
251 struct {
252 unsigned char cmd_type, pad0, pad1, pad2;
253 } header;
254 struct {
255 unsigned char cmd_type, count, reglo, reghi;
256 } packet0;
257 struct {
258 unsigned char cmd_type, count, adrlo, adrhi;
259 } vpu;
260 struct {
261 unsigned char cmd_type, packet, pad0, pad1;
262 } packet3;
263 struct {
264 unsigned char cmd_type, packet;
265 unsigned short count; /* amount of packet2 to emit */
266 } delay;
267 struct {
268 unsigned char cmd_type, buf_idx, pad0, pad1;
269 } dma;
270 struct {
271 unsigned char cmd_type, flags, pad0, pad1;
272 } wait;
273 struct {
274 unsigned char cmd_type, reg, n_bufs, flags;
275 } scratch;
276 struct {
277 unsigned char cmd_type, count, adrlo, adrhi_flags;
278 } r500fp;
279} drm_r300_cmd_header_t;

315/* There are 2 heaps (local/GART). Each region within a heap is a
316 * minimum of 64k, and there are at most 64 of them per heap.
317 */
318#define RADEON_LOCAL_TEX_HEAP 0
319#define RADEON_GART_TEX_HEAP 1
320#define RADEON_NR_TEX_HEAPS 2
321#define RADEON_NR_TEX_REGIONS 64
322#define RADEON_LOG_TEX_GRANULARITY 16
323
324#define RADEON_MAX_TEXTURE_LEVELS 12
325#define RADEON_MAX_TEXTURE_UNITS 3
326
327#define RADEON_MAX_SURFACES 8
328
329/* Blits have strict offset rules. All blit offset must be aligned on
330 * a 1K-byte boundary.
331 */
332#define RADEON_OFFSET_SHIFT 10
333#define RADEON_OFFSET_ALIGN (1 << RADEON_OFFSET_SHIFT)
334#define RADEON_OFFSET_MASK (RADEON_OFFSET_ALIGN - 1)

338typedef struct {
339 unsigned int red;
340 unsigned int green;
341 unsigned int blue;
342 unsigned int alpha;
343} radeon_color_regs_t;

345typedef struct {
346 /* Context state */
347 unsigned int pp_misc; /* 0x1c14 */
348 unsigned int pp_fog_color;
349 unsigned int re_solid_color;
350 unsigned int rb3d_blendcntl;
351 unsigned int rb3d_depthoffset;
352 unsigned int rb3d_depthpitch;
353 unsigned int rb3d_zstencilcntl;
354
355 unsigned int pp_cntl; /* 0x1c38 */
356 unsigned int rb3d_cntl;
357 unsigned int rb3d_coloroffset;
358 unsigned int re_width_height;
359 unsigned int rb3d_colorpitch;
360 unsigned int se_cntl;
361
362 /* Vertex format state */
363 unsigned int se_coord_fmt; /* 0x1c50 */
364
365 /* Line state */
366 unsigned int re_line_pattern; /* 0x1cd0 */
367 unsigned int re_line_state;
368
369 unsigned int se_line_width; /* 0x1db8 */
370
371 /* Bumpmap state */
372 unsigned int pp_lum_matrix; /* 0x1d00 */
373
374 unsigned int pp_rot_matrix_0; /* 0x1d58 */
375 unsigned int pp_rot_matrix_1;
376
377 /* Mask state */
378 unsigned int rb3d_stencilrefmask; /* 0x1d7c */
379 unsigned int rb3d_ropcntl;
380 unsigned int rb3d_planemask;
381
382 /* Viewport state */
383 unsigned int se_vport_xscale; /* 0x1d98 */
384 unsigned int se_vport_xoffset;
385 unsigned int se_vport_yscale;
386 unsigned int se_vport_yoffset;
387 unsigned int se_vport_zscale;
388 unsigned int se_vport_zoffset;
389
390 /* Setup state */
391 unsigned int se_cntl_status; /* 0x2140 */
392
393 /* Misc state */
394 unsigned int re_top_left; /* 0x26c0 */
395 unsigned int re_misc;
396} drm_radeon_context_regs_t;

398typedef struct {

404/* Setup registers for each texture unit
405 */

407 unsigned int pp_txfilter;

415
416typedef struct {
417 unsigned int start;
418 unsigned int finish;
419 unsigned int prim:8;
420 unsigned int stateidx:8;
421 unsigned int numverts:16; /* overloaded as offset/64 for elt prims */
422 unsigned int vc_format; /* vertex format */
423} drm_radeon_prim_t;
424
425typedef struct {
426 drm_radeon_context_regs_t context;
427 drm_radeon_texture_regs_t tex[RADEON_MAX_TEXTURE_UNITS];
428 drm_radeon_context2_regs_t context2;
429 unsigned int dirty;
430} drm_radeon_state_t;
431
432typedef struct {
433 /* The channel for communication of state information to the
434 * kernel on firing a vertex buffer with either of the
435 * obsoleted vertex/index ioctls.
436 */
437 drm_radeon_context_regs_t context_state;
438 drm_radeon_texture_regs_t tex_state[RADEON_MAX_TEXTURE_UNITS];
439 unsigned int dirty;
440 unsigned int vertsize;
441 unsigned int vc_format;
442
443 /* The current cliprects, or a subset thereof.
444 */
445 struct drm_clip_rect boxes[RADEON_NR_SAREA_CLIPRECTS];
446 unsigned int nbox;
447
448 /* Counters for client-side throttling of rendering clients.
449 */
450 unsigned int last_frame;
451 unsigned int last_dispatch;
452 unsigned int last_clear;
453
454 struct drm_tex_region tex_list[RADEON_NR_TEX_HEAPS][RADEON_NR_TEX_REGIONS +
455 1];
456 unsigned int tex_age[RADEON_NR_TEX_HEAPS];
457 int ctx_owner;
458 int pfState; /* number of 3d windows (0,1,2ormore) */
459 int pfCurrentPage; /* which buffer is being displayed? */
460 int crtc2_base; /* CRTC2 frame offset */
461 int tiling_enabled; /* set by drm, read by 2d + 3d clients */
462} drm_radeon_sarea_t;

472 */

474#define DRM_RADEON_CP_START 0x01
475#define DRM_RADEON_CP_STOP 0x02
476#define DRM_RADEON_CP_RESET 0x03
477#define DRM_RADEON_CP_IDLE 0x04
478#define DRM_RADEON_RESET 0x05

480#define DRM_RADEON_SWAP 0x07
481#define DRM_RADEON_CLEAR 0x08
482#define DRM_RADEON_VERTEX 0x09
483#define DRM_RADEON_INDICES 0x0A
484#define DRM_RADEON_NOT_USED
485#define DRM_RADEON_STIPPLE 0x0C
486#define DRM_RADEON_INDIRECT 0x0D
487#define DRM_RADEON_TEXTURE 0x0E
488#define DRM_RADEON_VERTEX2 0x0F
489#define DRM_RADEON_CMDBUF 0x10
490#define DRM_RADEON_GETPARAM 0x11
491#define DRM_RADEON_FLIP 0x12
492#define DRM_RADEON_ALLOC 0x13
493#define DRM_RADEON_FREE 0x14
494#define DRM_RADEON_INIT_HEAP 0x15
495#define DRM_RADEON_IRQ_EMIT 0x16
496#define DRM_RADEON_IRQ_WAIT 0x17
497#define DRM_RADEON_CP_RESUME 0x18
498#define DRM_RADEON_SETPARAM 0x19
499#define DRM_RADEON_SURF_ALLOC 0x1a
500#define DRM_RADEON_SURF_FREE 0x1b
501/* KMS ioctl */
502#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_INFO 0x1c
503#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_CREATE 0x1d
504#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_MMAP 0x1e
505#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_PREAD 0x21
506#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_PWRITE 0x22
507#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_SET_DOMAIN 0x23
508#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_WAIT_IDLE 0x24
509#define DRM_RADEON_CS 0x26
510#define DRM_RADEON_INFO 0x27
511#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_SET_TILING 0x28
512#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_GET_TILING 0x29
513#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_BUSY 0x2a
514#define DRM_RADEON_GEM_VA 0x2b
